1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:16,067
[CHILL MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,567
This wall is everything.

3
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:23,100
Recognition.

4
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:24,300
Proof you've mattered.

5
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:26,600
Proof that even if no one cared
when you were around,

6
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,067
it still counted.

7
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:33,400
Losers.

8
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,033
They scream,

9
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:37,367
"Pick me, I'm going to work
myself to death."

10
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:41,667
You want to be up there,
don't you?

11
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:42,633
[SCOFFS]

12
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:44,000
Yeah, right!

13
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:45,767
Don't judge.

14
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:47,567
Let me guess,

15
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:50,267
mama worked too much
so the trophies did the hugging.

16
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:55,333
<i>- Good night! Love you.
- God bless.</i>

17
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:00,233
[SIGHS]

18
00:01:03,233 --> 00:01:05,267
Why'd they stop at 2019?

19
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:06,567
Oh!

20
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,067
Ward One always won.

21
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:12,133
So they started rotating
the noms between the wards.

22
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:15,500
When it was finally time
for Ward Five... Boom!

23
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:16,533
COVID.

24
00:01:17,267 --> 00:01:19,800
So we still have a turn?

25
00:01:20,567 --> 00:01:23,233
[GIRLS LAUGHING IN THE DISTANCE]
Oh my god!

26
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,533
- Cheers!
- Smell that?

27
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:27,067
Ugh! Ward One!

28
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:35,100
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

29
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,033
[LAUGHING]

30
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:43,633
Oh! It's Ward Five!

31
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:45,433
Bless your hearts.

32
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:49,467
You guys try so hard
with so very little.

33
00:01:49,467 --> 00:01:50,733
Congrats on your win.

34
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:55,367
Oh my god. That's so old.

35
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:57,533
- That was before your botox.
- That was before your botox.

36
00:01:58,267 --> 00:01:59,533
Don't worry, Zeny.

37
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:02,133
You are so winning it again
this year.

38
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:05,100
- You're the best!
- You're the best!

39
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:08,333
I thought it was our turn
to nominate someone.

40
00:02:08,767 --> 00:02:10,833
Oh, that's so cute.

41
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:12,467
It's a relaunch.

42
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:15,367
You know, they have
to start the bar so high.

43
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,533
You get it?

44
00:02:16,533 --> 00:02:18,667
Well, you guys have
a fabulous day.

45
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:20,500
Enjoy! Bye!

46
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:22,400
- Take care!
- [CHUCKLING]

47
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,700
They suck!

48
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:28,467
Yup.

49
00:02:28,467 --> 00:02:30,800
But if this is a competition,
I can suck harder.

50
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,767
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

51
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:38,133
"Ward War One"

52
00:02:38,133 --> 00:02:45,167
[CHILL MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:02:45,167 --> 00:02:46,667
Are you paging me on my break?

54
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,900
I just want to talk
about the wall.

55
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:51,800
No, Noa.
I am not touching this.

56
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,700
I learned during my first
marriage to pick my battles.

57
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,500
I just want you
to do the right thing.

58
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:58,267
I mean, it was our
turn to nominate.

59
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:00,167
Walls don't save anyone.

60
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:03,767
Correct. They should call it
the wall of the best ass-kisser.

61
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:07,167
Huh! Says here,
kids without emotional support

62
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:09,800
grow up to be obsessive
overachievers.

63
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,867
Wild!

64
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:12,267
Back in my day,

65
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:15,567
good job only meant I got
the softer side of the broom.

66
00:03:15,567 --> 00:03:16,667
If you want to fix this,

67
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:18,267
you have to take it up
with Walt.

68
00:03:18,867 --> 00:03:21,833
He's still twitching after
your little speech last week.

69
00:03:21,867 --> 00:03:23,400
Any other options?

70
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,500
How about go
back to actual work?

71
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,433
You don't.

72
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:28,967
Unless Ward One
gives it up willingly,

73
00:03:28,967 --> 00:03:30,333
you have none.

74
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:32,867
Let me get back to this article.

75
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:39,167
Oh, no.
That look is dangerous.

76
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:46,700
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

77
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,967
Fans, tag this on ABS-CBN

78
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:50,633
because it might see it
on TV Patrol.

79
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:53,367
Tess, you better not be
scaring me. I swear to God!

80
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:54,767
There's no such thing as ghosts.

81
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:57,233
Oh, it's a rat!
Oh my god, I hate rats!

82
00:03:57,233 --> 00:03:58,500
Okay, pause.

83
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:00,733
Don, I just got verified,

84
00:04:00,733 --> 00:04:03,700
so please don't tank it
with an unsmart vibe.

85
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:05,900
I'm... I'm smart.

86
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,833
Big talk for someone
who thought "triage"

87
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,233
was a dirty French word.

88
00:04:09,933 --> 00:04:12,400
- [GASPS] It's moving!
- Okay, that's it!

89
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,933
Camille, you're being so mean.

90
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:16,900
Well, it's not my fault that
I have a reputation to uphold.

91
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:19,500
Okay, Tess, if you think
you're scaring me,

92
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,500
I'll show you scared.

93
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,733
- [GRUNTING]
- [MAN] Ow, ow, ow!

94
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:26,467
Dude!

95
00:04:26,467 --> 00:04:27,800
What's wrong with you?!

96
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:30,267
You almost activated
DonDon's brain cells.

97
00:04:30,867 --> 00:04:34,233
If this is what double overtime
is like. I'm out.

98
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:37,433
And just a gentle reminder,

99
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:40,600
screaming in the ward
sends the wrong message.

100
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,567
What? That it's haunted?

101
00:04:42,567 --> 00:04:44,733
Oh, well, I know a healer.

102
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:46,967
She can wipe this place
clean like a ghost buster.

103
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,067
No!

104
00:04:48,067 --> 00:04:50,467
I liked him better when
he pretended

105
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:52,400
he couldn't speak English.

106
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,967
You guys would
make a cute couple.

107
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:55,500
No, they don't.

108
00:04:56,333 --> 00:05:00,600
Just to remind everyone,
there's no such thing as ghosts.

109
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,633
Right! Like there's
no such thing

110
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:05,833
as too pretty to be straight.

111
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,733
Moving on,

112
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:11,333
I do have another surprise
for everyone.

113
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:14,367
Ward Five has been
invisible for long enough.

114
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:17,733
People give everything to this
place and still get forgotten.

115
00:05:18,367 --> 00:05:20,333
But not this year.

116
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:22,067
So please welcome...

117
00:05:22,067 --> 00:05:26,600
[VOCALIZATION] Ooh! Ooh!

118
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:30,333
It's not my fault
that you can see ghosts.

119
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:32,000
[SMOOCHES]

120
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,300
[VOCALIZATION] Ooh! Ooh!

121
00:05:34,967 --> 00:05:38,500
What I was saying was,
I have a special guest--

122
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,467
What she's saying is,

123
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:44,800
as kind and considerate
as we are in Ward One,

124
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:48,300
we had no clue that this
nomination meant so much to you.

125
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:52,533
And because we are
kind and considerate,

126
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:54,767
- I decided--
- We! [CHUCKLES]

127
00:05:54,767 --> 00:05:56,667
We decided.

128
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:59,500
That a friendly competition
for the nom

129
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:02,033
would be the
most elegant solution.

130
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:03,033
Dumb!

131
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,633
We're going to break
it down to--

132
00:06:05,633 --> 00:06:07,500
Two categories.

133
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,900
- First, academic.
- Brains!

134
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,833
Smartest person wins.

135
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:14,933
Would you prefer
to explain it, dear?

136
00:06:14,933 --> 00:06:17,400
Oh, no. You're the guest.
Go ahead.

137
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,700
Wait, wait! I want to be
the smart thing or,

138
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:20,900
you know, whatever.

139
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:25,600
Sweetie, it's trivia.
It doesn't have glitters on it.

140
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,567
- I know.
- Okay?

141
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,833
So, can I do it?

142
00:06:29,867 --> 00:06:32,500
Ooh...
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

143
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,100
- Okay.
- Done!

144
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:38,100
Then second, we're going to
have a practical skills contest.

145
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,800
[YAWNS]

146
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,567
Oh, there you go,
pretty boy volunteers!

147
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,400
What? No, I was just stretching.

148
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,667
But, anything for you, Noa.

149
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:47,100
There we have it!

150
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:52,867
Oh, but just so we're clear...

151
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:56,100
If you guys lose...

152
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:57,967
Nothing changes.

153
00:06:58,633 --> 00:06:59,933
Bye!

154
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:04,900
[SIGHS] Don't we have
a say in this?

155
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,667
We can win this thing!

156
00:07:07,067 --> 00:07:08,033
Right?

157
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:09,800
Left!

158
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:19,667
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:25,100
- Oh, DonDon, wait!
- Oh, hey, Noa!

160
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,600
- Dear, I can feel...
- Not now, Mom!

161
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,433
...that you're planning-- Ugh!

162
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:30,900
- Hi!
- I'm so ready for tomorrow.

163
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:32,467
Yeah, about tomorrow...

164
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,000
I should do it.

165
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,667
Why? Am I going to get sick?

166
00:07:36,633 --> 00:07:38,733
Nose is clear.
I still got this. Look.

167
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:40,700
My flashcards
even have emojis.

168
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:43,800
- Great! [CHUCKLES]
- Thank you!

169
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,100
Not great.

170
00:07:49,533 --> 00:07:52,033
Neural foraminal stenosis.

171
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,467
Hmm-- Oh.

172
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:01,733
[SIGHS]

173
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:06,733
You could just apologize,
you know.

174
00:08:07,767 --> 00:08:09,533
[SCOFFS, INHALES]

175
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:13,133
I hate it that everything
is about me.

176
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:18,067
Dude, she's killing herself
trying to prove to everyone

177
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:20,667
that she is not the idiot
they all think she is.

178
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,800
Well, have you
heard what Ros says?

179
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,800
Yes, I know.

180
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:26,600
Ros's love language
is literally bullying.

181
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,600
But at least she doesn't
spend her whole day

182
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,933
caring about what everyone
thinks about her online.

183
00:08:39,067 --> 00:08:43,600
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,500
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome back to Ward Wars!

185
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:53,233
[CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

186
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,667
As you know, I'm your host,
Gavin Graziano,

187
00:08:56,667 --> 00:08:57,767
here from Ward One.

188
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:00,300
[CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

189
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:03,633
And trying to keep up...
Ward Five.

190
00:09:03,633 --> 00:09:05,733
- Yeah, DonDon!
- You got this!

191
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:08,767
- [CHEERING, APPLAUDING]
- [CROWD BOOS]

192
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:10,033
- Yoo-hoo!
- [APPLAUSE]

193
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:11,233
[GAVIN] Our next question.

194
00:09:12,233 --> 00:09:16,033
This is the largest organ
in the human body.

195
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:17,767
- [BUZZER]
- Skin.

196
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:19,667
That is correct!

197
00:09:19,667 --> 00:09:24,267
[CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

198
00:09:24,267 --> 00:09:25,533
[DINGS]

199
00:09:25,867 --> 00:09:29,533
This amoeba lives in warm lakes

200
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:32,833
and enters the human body
through the nose.

201
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:35,933
- [BUZZER]
- Naegleria Fowleri?

202
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:42,800
[CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

203
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:44,633
[DINGS]

204
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:48,800
[CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

205
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:51,167
You know,
maybe you should just quit.

206
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,600
You're embarrassing yourself.

207
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:55,267
[GAVIN] Next question.

208
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:57,767
Time out!

209
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:00,867
You suck!

210
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:02,700
Are time-outs allowed?

211
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,033
You know what? Why not?

212
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,333
Beats going back
to the supply room.

213
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:08,367
I knew that. I really did.

214
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:09,700
Hey, it's okay.

215
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,833
If you want,
I'll play the next round.

216
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,233
You don't trust me.

217
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,167
I do.

218
00:10:20,067 --> 00:10:22,200
Just not with this one.

219
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:25,967
I really tried.

220
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,800
- [SLAPS]
- [NOA GASPS]

221
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,067
Mom!

222
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,867
You're really something.

223
00:10:35,867 --> 00:10:39,167
Because of your foolishness,
my ghost powers have leveled up.

224
00:10:40,633 --> 00:10:43,267
Are you okay?

225
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:46,033
[TESS] Look down.

226
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,700
Down!

227
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:59,233
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:11:01,867 --> 00:11:05,933
Because of a tiny technicality,
yesterday was a draw!

229
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:07,100
Yay, us!

230
00:11:09,433 --> 00:11:11,400
Let's all give DonDon
a round of applause

231
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,833
for a job well done!

232
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:13,900
[CLAPS]

233
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,333
Good news.

234
00:11:17,933 --> 00:11:19,433
I'll be playing the final round.

235
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:21,367
Wait. I thought it was me.

236
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:24,433
I realized I need to set
a better example.

237
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:27,700
So, who knows the game
better than me, right, guys?

238
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:30,067
Sorry.

239
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:31,133
No.

240
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:34,133
Can we go back to work now?

241
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,700
Yeah.

242
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,300
Don't just go there alone.

244
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,900
You saw them. It's fine.

245
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:51,733
I'm going to show them
how it's done.

246
00:11:51,733 --> 00:11:54,800
Their wall is just
a popularity contest.

247
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:55,933
Hi!

248
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:58,100
At some point, you're going
to have to let me lead

249
00:11:58,100 --> 00:11:59,000
the way I lead.

250
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,433
Oh, right.
You're already old enough.

251
00:12:01,433 --> 00:12:02,933
Okay. Lead.

252
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:16,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:31,800
Welcome...

254
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,767
to the Wheelchair Navigation
Transport Obstacle Course.

255
00:12:35,467 --> 00:12:37,067
Where's your pit crew?

256
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:38,900
I only see Ward One here.

257
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,100
Oh, great! You made it!

258
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:44,767
Teamwork makes
the dream work, right?

259
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,433
Team?

260
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:48,733
What?

261
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:51,500
You didn't read the email?

262
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,067
You're allowed help.

263
00:12:53,067 --> 00:12:54,767
It's really intuitive.

264
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:57,867
Let's go to positions, everyone!

265
00:12:57,867 --> 00:13:04,267
[CHEERING]

266
00:13:07,367 --> 00:13:14,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

267
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:31,967
[CHEERING]

268
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:38,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:44,200
[CHEERING]

270
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:51,200
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

271
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:12,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:12,967 --> 00:14:15,133
[CHEERING]

273
00:14:15,133 --> 00:14:22,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

274
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:43,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

275
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,567
[CHEERING]

276
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:52,100
[MUSIC STOPS]

277
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:56,067
[CHEERING]

278
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:00,900
Chocolates from Dubai!

279
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:04,567
- Ask me anything.
- What?

280
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,400
Ask me anything medical-related.

281
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,567
Parasitology? Virology?

282
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:10,067
Biochemistry?

283
00:15:10,067 --> 00:15:11,633
Nursing standard basics?

284
00:15:11,633 --> 00:15:13,500
I don't need to, DonDon.

285
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,567
Come on!

286
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:17,400
Fine. Measles.

287
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,567
Paramyxovirus.

288
00:15:20,267 --> 00:15:23,267
Immune amnesia,
which has the ability to

289
00:15:23,267 --> 00:15:24,600
- wipe out like, 70%...
- DonDon.

290
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,467
- DonDon.
- What? Look!

291
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,667
Camille! I'm not dumb, okay?

292
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:30,967
I know it takes me a while
to learn things.

293
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:32,567
But I do remember things.

294
00:15:32,567 --> 00:15:36,567
I also know how hard it is
to study to become an RA.

295
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,200
You know, I never overreact.

296
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:40,567
- I just did...
- Never?

297
00:15:42,433 --> 00:15:43,567
I was there.

298
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:44,967
No, you weren't.

299
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,300
You're lucky I stream
everything. Look.

300
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:52,700
[PEOPLE CHEERING ON VIDEO]

301
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:54,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

302
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,900
Wait.

303
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:58,700
Is that that Ward One chick

304
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:01,333
unplugging my buzzer
before the game begins?

305
00:16:03,167 --> 00:16:05,167
Are you thinking what
I'm thinking?

306
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,333
Am I supposed to be
thinking right now?

307
00:16:25,733 --> 00:16:27,567
You're really my daughter.
I hate losing.

308
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:29,200
I hate losing.

309
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:34,133
I didn't do this for me.

310
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:42,300
You gave everything
to this place.

311
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,533
Every birthday.

312
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:48,333
Every track meet.

313
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:51,233
Every play.

314
00:16:57,667 --> 00:16:58,667
I thought...

315
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:01,200
if I could get you up there...

316
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:03,967
then maybe it meant something.

317
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:09,467
Maybe you didn't miss
my life for nothing.

318
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:15,533
Saying this out loud...

319
00:17:17,433 --> 00:17:18,500
[SIGHS]

320
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,233
Maybe I was doing it for me.

321
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:23,433
I just got tired of needing
anyone.

322
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:30,200
I have no partner, Noa.

323
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:40,567
Maybe you're right.

324
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:43,567
I should've stopped overworking
myself from time to time.

325
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:48,333
You?

326
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,133
You're actually admitting
you're wrong?

327
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,433
Yeah.

328
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:55,467
You're right.

329
00:17:57,133 --> 00:17:58,333
But I'm wrong?

330
00:17:58,333 --> 00:17:59,500
Never.

331
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,200
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

332
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:09,300
They hate me, don't they?

333
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,233
Who could hate you?

334
00:18:16,367 --> 00:18:18,167
What would I do
without you, Mom?

335
00:18:24,367 --> 00:18:25,333
Go on.

336
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:26,800
Talk to them.

337
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:31,467
[EXHALES DEEPLY] You're right.

338
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:48,600
I love you.

339
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:51,133
Yeah.

340
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:52,800
Okay.

341
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:11,133
I've been looking all over
the place for you guys.

342
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:15,467
We heard what happened.

343
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:18,133
Word travels fast when you
face plant in front of Ward One.

344
00:19:18,767 --> 00:19:20,333
You didn't think I could do it.

345
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:21,400
Or me.

346
00:19:22,233 --> 00:19:23,400
That's not why.

347
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,433
Then why?

348
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,567
I messed up.

349
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:34,800
This whole thing was so I
could get my mom the nomination.

350
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:38,567
That's why everything
felt so off.

351
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:40,733
You could've just told us.

352
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:41,900
I know.

353
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:45,833
Sometimes we forget
that we're not alone.

354
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:49,567
And we need other people.

355
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:53,467
Hey, I have evidence
that it was rigged.

356
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:55,900
We showed up to the practicals,
but there weren't any.

357
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,533
And then we heard
it was changed

358
00:19:57,533 --> 00:19:59,800
to some stupid obstacle course
somewhere else.

359
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,667
Wait. You guys showed up?

360
00:20:03,533 --> 00:20:04,600
Are you deaf?

361
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:08,433
- Oh, my God.
- Hey, hey, hey.

362
00:20:08,433 --> 00:20:09,800
Is this necessary?

363
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:10,967
Group hug!

364
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:13,800
- Come here.
- No, no, no.

365
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:14,800
[GIGGLING]

366
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:21,767
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,933
You might have a strong case.

368
00:20:28,433 --> 00:20:30,633
Who wants to help me
break the news to Ward One?

369
00:20:30,633 --> 00:20:31,667
[ROS] Me, me, me!

370
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:33,333
[JANE] We got to pull
those lashes one by one!

371
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,767
[CHUCKLING]

372
00:20:37,433 --> 00:20:44,400
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:48,467
Great.

374
00:20:48,467 --> 00:20:52,733
Hey! Whatever deal you guys had,
I heard it wasn't fair.

375
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:55,333
Yeah, Camille's even live
streaming about it right now.

376
00:20:55,333 --> 00:20:58,733
You lost, you sexy,
beautiful a-hole.

377
00:20:58,733 --> 00:21:01,333
Sorry, guys. I already
submitted to the board.

378
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:02,300
What?

379
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:04,700
Why wasn't I CC'd on this?

380
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,567
You should know
how this place works.

381
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:07,967
[DONDON] Well, you cheated!
You're a cheater.

382
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,967
(In Spanish) And you're a tramp!

383
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:13,467
Excellence always rises.

384
00:21:14,267 --> 00:21:17,233
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have patients to attend to.

385
00:21:17,733 --> 00:21:19,300
Oh, heads up.

386
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:23,267
That rotation thing didn't
survive the relaunch.

387
00:21:23,267 --> 00:21:24,400
Bye.

388
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:29,700
- Oh, no, no, no!
- No! Don't! Ros!

389
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:37,367
So, Ward Five may never
get a nomination...

390
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:39,600
But we made our own.

391
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:51,433
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

392
00:21:51,433 --> 00:21:52,400
[ROS] Wait.

393
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:54,967
Why does she look constipated?

394
00:21:56,433 --> 00:21:57,800
I edited it.

395
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:02,100
You know.

396
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:05,633
I kind of feel jealous that
only her picture is up there.

397
00:22:05,833 --> 00:22:06,933
But...

398
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:09,567
Considering that
she'll never win again...

399
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:10,600
why not?

400
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:13,400
Well deserved.

401
00:22:14,067 --> 00:22:15,367
We miss you, Tess!

402
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:19,100
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

403
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:22,633
That's not even important to me!
You guys are like idiots!

404
00:22:34,067 --> 00:22:41,033
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

405
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:55,800
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

406
00:23:10,833 --> 00:23:17,800
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

407
00:23:32,867 --> 00:23:39,800
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

408
00:23:54,833 --> 00:24:01,800
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

409
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:23,800
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

410
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:45,833
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

411
